      <div class="article-teaser">
        The budget on 8 July brings about further change for pensions.
        
      </div>
    
    <div class="on-this-page">
      <p>The key announcements impacting pensions were:</p>
<h3>Annual Allowance</h3>
<p>The Input Period will be aligned to the tax year, this means that for the year to 5 April 2016 there will be transitional arrangements, which provide a higher Annual Allowance for the period 1 April 2015 to 5 April 2016<br />
From the 2016/17 tax year, for those with income exceeding &pound;150,000 from all sources, not just salary, the Annual Allowance will be reduced by &pound;1 for every &pound;2 of income over &pound;150,000, to a minimum of &pound;10,000</p>
<h3>Lifetime Allowance (LTA)</h3>
<p>It was confirmed that, with effect from 6 April 2016, the LTA will reduce from &pound;1.25 million to &pound;1 million. Transitional protection will be introduced, alongside this reduction, for those with pension rights already over &pound;1 million<br />
With effect from 6 April 2018, the LTA will be indexed annually in line with the Consumer Prices Index</p>
<p>Once further details become available we will update the website.</p>
<p>13 July 2015</p>
      
           
      
      
        
          
